import pandas as pd
# Load the dataset from MD Science Center
fn_o_c = "C:/Users/jenna/OneDrive/Desktop/Fall 2025/Energy Meterology/Final Proj/data/City_Hist_Data.csv"
df_o_c = pd.read_csv(fn_o_c)

df_o_c['DATE'] = pd.to_datetime(df_o_c['DATE'])
df_cleaned_o_c = df_o_c.dropna(subset=['TAVG']).copy()

# Filter and convert to Celsius (C = (F - 32) * 5/9)
start_date = '1999-01-01'
end_date = '2014-12-31'
df_filtered_o_c = df_cleaned_o_c[(df_cleaned_o_c['DATE'] >= start_date) & (df_cleaned_o_c['DATE'] <= end_date)].copy()
df_filtered_o_c['TAVG_C'] = (df_filtered_o_c['TAVG'] - 32) * 5/9
df_filtered_o_c['DATE'] = pd.to_datetime(df_filtered_o_c['DATE'])

print(df_filtered_o_c)

import matplotlib.dates as mdates
import cftime

# Convert df_filtered DATE to datetime
df_filtered_o_c['DATE'] = pd.to_datetime(df_filtered_o_c['DATE'])

# Convert cftime.DatetimeNoLeap to matplotlib numeric dates
ts_time_nums_h_c = mdates.date2num([pd.Timestamp(str(t)) for t in ts_h_c['time'].values])

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12,6))

# Plot ts
ax.plot(ts_time_nums_h_c, ts_h_c.values, color='orange', label='Average Surface Temp (Historical CMIP Data)')

# Plot df_filtered
ax.plot(df_filtered_o_c['DATE'], df_filtered_o_c['TAVG_C'], color='g', label='Average Surface Temp (MD Science Center Obs Data)')

# Format x-axis as dates
ax.xaxis_date()
ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(mdates.YearLocator(2))  # tick every 2 years
ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(mdates.DateFormatter('%Y'))

ax.set_xlabel("Date")
ax.set_ylabel("Temperature (C)")
ax.set_title("Historical Daily Temperature at MD Science Center")
ax.legend()
ax.grid(True)

plt.show()
plt.savefig("Hist_tas_Comapare_Obs.CMIP_City.png")

import numpy as np
from scipy.stats import pearsonr

# ts dates as just date
ts_df_h_c = pd.DataFrame({
    'DATE': [pd.Timestamp(str(t)).date() for t in ts_h_c['time'].values],
    'tas_C': ts_h_c.values
})

# df_filtered dates as just date
df_filtered_o_c['DATE_ONLY'] = df_filtered_o_c['DATE'].dt.date

# Merge on just the date
merged_city = pd.merge(ts_df_h_c, df_filtered_o_c[['DATE_ONLY', 'TAVG_C']], 
                  left_on='DATE', right_on='DATE_ONLY', how='inner')

# Now calculate correlation
from scipy.stats import pearsonr

r_c, p_value_c = pearsonr(merged_city['tas_C'], merged_city['TAVG_C'])
print(f"Pearson r: {r_c:.4f}")

Pearson r: 0.7906

Bias Correction

City

In[12]:
from sklearn.isotonic import IsotonicRegression

# Ensure DATE columns are datetime and align by day
df_filtered_o_c['DATE'] = pd.to_datetime(df_filtered_o_c['DATE'])
ts_df_h_c['DATE'] = pd.to_datetime(ts_df_h_c['DATE'])
df_filtered_o_c = df_filtered_o_c.sort_values('DATE')
ts_df_h_c = ts_df_h_c.sort_values('DATE')

# Merge on DATE to align model and observed data
merged_city = pd.merge(ts_df_h_c, df_filtered_o_c, on='DATE', suffixes=('_model', '_obs'))

# Extract values
model_t_city = merged_city['tas_C'].values  # CMIP historical data
obs_t_city = merged_city['TAVG_C'].values     # observed city temps

# Quantile mapping: fit isotonic regression between model and observed distributions
iso_city = IsotonicRegression(out_of_bounds='clip')
iso_city.fit(model_t_city, obs_t_city)

# Apply correction
merged_city['tas_C_corrected'] = iso_city.predict(model_t_city)

# Plot before/after correction
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 5))
plt.scatter(model_t_city, obs_t_city, alpha=0.4, label='Before Correction')
plt.scatter(model_t_city, merged_city['tas_C_corrected'], alpha=0.4, label='After Correction', color='r')
plt.xlabel('Model Temperature (C)')
plt.ylabel('Observed Temperature (C)')
plt.legend()
plt.title('Bias Correction via Quantile Mapping')
plt.show()
plt.savefig("Hist_tas_BiasCorrection_City.png")

<Figure size 640x480 with 0 Axes>

Compute Bias-Corrected UHI

In[16]:
# Merge the city and BWI corrected datasets by DATE
uhi_merged = pd.merge(
    merged_city[['DATE', 'tas_C_corrected']], 
    merged_rural[['DATE', 'tas_C_corrected']], 
    on='DATE', 
    suffixes=('_city', '_rural')
)

# Calculate bias-corrected UHI
uhi_merged['UHI_corrected'] = uhi_merged['tas_C_corrected_city'] - uhi_merged['tas_C_corrected_rural']

uhi_median = uhi_merged['UHI_corrected'].median()

plt.figure(figsize=(12,5))
plt.plot(uhi_merged['DATE'], uhi_merged['UHI_corrected'], color='purple', label='Bias-Corrected UHI')
plt.axhline(uhi_median, color='black', linestyle='--', linewidth=1, label='Median UHI')
plt.text(uhi_merged['DATE'].iloc[-50], uhi_median + 0.05, f"{uhi_median:.2f}C", color='black', fontsize=10, va='bottom')
plt.xlabel('Date')
plt.ylabel('Temperature Difference (C)')
plt.title('Bias-Corrected Urban Heat Island (City - Rural)')
plt.legend()
plt.minorticks_on()
plt.grid()
plt.grid(which='minor', linestyle=':', linewidth='0.2', color='gray')
plt.show()
plt.savefig("Hist_tas_BiasCorrection_UHI.png")
